						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar setup in front of the agasi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">17th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record mentions only the cyclic year Āngīrasa. It reads the fixation of the quantity of Paddy and ghee to be given by the <hi rend="italic">vokkalus</hi> [cultivators] during the specified period for the land leased. The fixation seems to be a general assessment for the entire village. Atanura, the village is mentioned in the record. The latter part of the record is much damaged. [See No. 334 above].</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 17th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
